Nick Hayes (nhayes@interaccess.com) writes:

> Where can I find the version of PGP that is available as shareware? (This is 

You can't. PGP can be obtained either as freeware, or commercially.
There are no shareware versions of it.

> correct right?) If not where can I buy it... please email back.

Check the FAQ for alt.security.pgp. The free versions of PGP are
available via ftp from about anywhere in the world, and the commercial
version is available only in the USA from ViaCrypt. I don't rememeber
ViaCrypt's address, but it is in the FAQ mentioned above.

Regards,
Vesselin
